name: St. Mary Magdalene's church day festivities
description: Plenty of tradition, real customs and welcoming hosts: the festival of St Mary Magdalene attracts hundreds of visitors each year. After the church service and subsequent festive procession Leutasch clubs and associations meet at the festival arena in the Leutasch hamlet of Kirchplatzl. A lively mixture of homemade farmers’ specialities, original dance music and friendly games make this church festival into an unforgettable experience.

name: 8th International Porsche "Karwendel Trophy"
description:
Porsche Club Tirol is hosting a second-to-none motorsport event in Seefeld!
Programme: Friday: until 5:00 pm, arrival, check-in and briefing of all participants; 7:00 pm, welcome reception with aperitif at the bar; 7:30 pm dinner; 9:00 pm, reception at Casino Seefeld. Saturday: from 9:30 am, positioning of all cars for the start, 9:45 am, single start every minute for all vehicles to roadbook guided excursion, 4:00 to 5:00 pm, finish at parking next to Krumers Post Hotel, 7:30 pm, "Porsche Night" with presentation ceremony at the hotel. Sunday: 9:00 am, positioning of all cars for the parade "Concours Elégance", 10:00 am, parade of all cars through Seefeld, 11:30 am, convivial get-together "Frühschoppen", conclusion and journey home. Detailed information and registration on www.karwendel-trophy.at.

name: 12th International RAIFFEISEN MOUNTAIN RUN
description:
RUN WITH THE MOST BREATH-TAKING SCENERY IN TYROL.  
Starting from the bottom station of the Rosshütte cable car, runners can choose between two different routes: the ‘Mountainrun’ involves almost 1,000 vertical metres, while the ‘Jedermann Run’ involves some 450 metres of altitude. All runners are welcome, from individual starters, to two-person teams, to bigger teams. Combined ranking with the Karwendel Mountain Run in Mittenwald possible. Organisation & inscription: Ski-Club Seefeld, Martin Mausser, tel.: 0660/6548630, e-mail: nennungen.ltss@ski-club-seefeld.com.

name: 21st Int. Senior Soccer Autumn Tournament
description: This year Seefeld is hosting the popular International Seniors’ Autumn Football Tournament for the 21st time. Eligible for participation are ‘seniors’ over the age of 30 and ‘veterans’ over the age of 40. The matches take place on the two well-maintained pitches in Seefeld’s sports stadium. We look forward to exciting competitions with motivated teams here in the heart of the Alps. Programme available in all information offices of Olympiaregion Seefeld and on www.seefeld.com.

name: Karwendel March
description:
„Karwendelmarsch“ long distance hike. Along a 52 km route to Pertisau or a 35 km route to Eng, the max. 2.500 participants can take the beauty of the Alpenpark Karwendel.
To allow ambitious hikers, Nordic walkers and runners to enjoy the impressive beauty of Karwendel  Alpine Nature Park, Olympiaregion Seefeld is organising the now legendary Karwendel March together with the Vitalregion Achensee region.
And in the high summer of 2017, the regions will once again be inviting participants to take part in a long distance march together. To do so, hikers will need to conquer paths leading to 2,281 metres in altitude (uphill). The route leads from a start in Scharnitz, via the Eng valley, to Pertisau am Achensee. The emphasis throughout is on providing a fascinating nature experience and strengthening visitors’ awareness of Karwendel Alpine Nature Park as a unique environment for numerous rare flora and fauna.

name: 18th IML – Unicorn Walk

location.name: Festhalle Wetterstein bei d. ErlebnisWelt Alpenbad

description: “Nos iungat ambulare” is the motto of the association of international amateur walkers, who cover 42km each day of the event. Start and finish line is in Leutasch, which allows the 2,000 participants to experience some of the most attractive routes in the area. The time taken is less important than the enjoyment of taking part. The Wetterstein event hall offers the opportunity for sociable companionship.

name: 19th Ganghofer Hubertus Week
description: Nature, culture and plenty of hunting lore: Monika and Hans Neuner, also known as “Bantl”, are guides to Ludwig Ganghofer‘s trail for a week. Themed walks, interesting events and special game recipes from the local cookbook have been a hit for almost 20 years.

name: 9th Days of Music in the Olympiaregion Seefeld - Festival of Classic Music
description: During the 9th Days of Music Festival, musicians of international renown will, once again, be treating music lovers to a superb repertoire of classical music. A diverse range of concerts will be performed in various venues and by various artists offering musical delights of the highest calibre.  As every year promoting the talents of budding young music lovers plays an important role during the festival. Detailed information is available from the information offices in the Olympiaregion Seefeld and on the websites www.seefeld.com and https://musiktage-seefeld.at.

name: 33th international team speed chess tournament
description:
At this year’s 34rd International Speed Chess Team Tournament in Leutasch, numerous teams will, once again, be battling it out on the board. Speed chess is a special type of chess in which the players have a total of only 10 to 60 minutes, during which they must complete all their moves. Teams will be competing for considerable sums of prize money, as well as other prizes with a regional focus. Information and regristration: Bernhard Jehle, Von-Thürheim-Str. 72, D-89264 Weisshorn
Tel. 0049 (0)7309-7999, Email: chessware@t-online.de, Website: www.chessware.de

name: Garden Party of Seefeld Fire Brigade
description: Further information and programme on www.ffseefeld.at.

name: FOREST FESTIVAL LIKE IN FORMER TIMES ORGANIZED BY THE CHOIR “STEINRÖSLER SÄNGER“
Kaltwasser Challenge 2017 - Fun Race
description: The "Kaltwasser" Challenge at the Rosshütte is a ‘just-for-fun’ contest for young and old alike. The competition comprises various disciplines, and contestants can choose between single and multiple starts. Each discipline is ranked separately. Adults can participate in mountain bike and e-bike races, Nordic walking and fell running, while kids take part in a junior cycle race and in the ‘cold-water’ run. Along with non-stop fun, there’s also plenty to eat and drink! Registration: Ski Club Seefeld, michaela.stark@ski-club-seefeld.com, tel. 0664 4608072, details on www.ski-club-seefeld.com.

name: Shopping & Wine
description: Enjoy the best Austrian wines of 16 top wine-growers in the stylish atmosphere of Seefeld´s shops, offering the latest fashion and shoe trends. For a tasting pass of € 19.00 only, you can try selected wines. The pass is available at the information office Seefeld, in all participating shops..

name: 6th Mountain Crystal Festival featuring Mario and Christoph
description:
Mario and Christoph, former members of the band Alpentrio Tirol, will be presenting the 6th Mountain Crystal Festival in Seefeld, a multi-day event to delight all fans of folk music and easy listening. With a wide spectrum of musical treats and a high-calibre line-up of artists, audiences can be sure of an unforgettable musical experience amid a fantastic ambience. 
Programme: 
Thursday: Welcome Evening at the Kurpark Seefeld, 5:00 pm, with presenter DJ Alex Weber & Ingo Rotter, the band “DÖT“, as well as Mario & Christoph. 
Friday: “Hit on Hit-Show” in the Casino WM Hall, 5:00 pm, DJ Alex Weber presents “Die Paldauer” Liane, Graziano, Melanie Payer und "Mario & Christoph". 
Saturday: “Hüttengaudi - fun in the mountains” at the panorama restaurant Rosshütte, from 11:00 am, free use of mountain railway Rosshütte, music & entertainment with "Die Rodensteiner", "all you can eat" offer at the restaurant. 
“Night of stars” in the Casino WM Hall, 5:00 pm, presenter Ingo Rotter leads through the programme with “Olaf, der Flipper“, Stefan Micha, Daniela Alfinito, Ronny Weiland and "Mario & Christoph". 
Sunday: “Radio U1 Frühschoppen”, at Casino WM Hall, from 11:00 am, programme: Ingo Rotter presents a programme with “Olaf, der Flipper“, the groups “Rodensteiner“ & “DÖT“, the “Geschwister Niederbacher” and "Mario & Christoph". Information, news and ticket prices on www.marioundchristoph.at.

name: summer market of Leutasch
description: Stroll around and enjoy life with pleasant company: the Leutasch market stalls offer traditional handicrafts and local specialities, all accompanied by folk music and a carefully-selected programme of events for children.

name: MOUNTAIN RUN “ZUGSPITZ ULTRATRAIL 2017"
description: More than 2,000 trail runners from 50 countries make the pilgrimage for this extreme run up the highest German mountain. The athletes conquer a total of up to 5,412 metres in altitude and a maximum distance of 101.6 km. There are five different routes to choose from, among them the ‘Supertrail’ (62.8 km, 2,923 metres in altitude) with its start in Leutasch. This challenging route winds its way through the notoriously beautiful scenery of the Leutasch Wetterstein mountain range. www.zugspitz-ultratrail.com

name: Seefeld Summer Concerts 2017
description:
The Seefeld Cultural Circle has once again organised a demanding concert programme in their expected professional manner for all fans of music
which will take place this summer between July and September. The theme “Baroque and modern times” raises expectations for the varied entertainment. The programme for individual concerts can be found in the Seefeld information office and they are also listed in the events calendar or can be found at www.seefeld.com.

name: White Secco White Night - Fashion & Lifestyle party
description: For years now the 14th August 2017 is a not-to-be-missed date for all lifestyle lovers and fashionistas in Seefeld. Organised by Seefeld’s retailers, the event showcases the very latest styles from Milan, Paris and London, and wows spectators with outfits ranging from hip to extravagant. During the White Night event, the entire pedestrian zone in Seefeld is transformed into a giant runway. The glamorous backdrop ensures a unique fashion festival complete with a party dress code - simply white! FREE ENTRANCE! Details on www.einkaufserlebnis.at.

name: 30th Int. Alpine Skat Tournament
description: At the Alpine Skat Tournament in Seefeld card-playing enthusiasts pit their wits against one another! Over a period of five days, competitors play three series of 48 games in accordance with international skat regulations. A total of € 20,000 in prize money awaits the participants in the single, overall, special and team rankings. Those guests accompanying the skat competitors are invited to participate in a four-day rummy tournament. The Alpine Skat Tournament partner hotels have special accommodation packages for the contestants for the duration of the tournament. More information & registration: Hans Imping, Schiefestr. 42, D-48599 Gronau, tel.: +49 (0) 171 27 40 587, e-Mail: labes-haget@t-online.de.

name: 10th GANGHOFER TRAIL
description: “Challenging, with great organisation, simply wonderful” - participants shower the popular running event with compliments. The half marathon route takes in the high valley of the Leutasch area on lovely wood and meadow trails. Even the shorter distance of 8km (Nordic walking also possible) passes landmarks such as the lake in Weidach or banks of the Leutasch stream. Smaller competitors can celebrate their first success by taking part in the 500m Mini Run or the 1.5km Junior Run.  www.ganghofertrail.at

name: Grand Strudel Festival of Seefeld´s publicans
description: Run by the local restaurateurs, the Strudel Festival in Seefeld’s pedestrian zone offers from 11:00 am a huge variety of tasty pastry treats, both sweet and savoury. From bite-size strudel tasters to Seefeld’s longest strudel, there are literally ‘oodles of strudels’ to taste your way through! Live and dancing music and children´s programme guarantee an entertaining day & evening! Programme and further information is provided in all information offices of Olympiaregion Seefeld and on www.seefeld.com.

name: 11th MOUNTAIN SPRING DAYS
description: Monika and Hans Neuner, also known as “Bantl”, have seen generations come and go in the Leutasch valley. Hardly anyone knows as many interesting tales about the nature, culture and history of the area as these two original locals. Walking together to the loveliest and historically most important spots in the region they offer special insights into their homeland. An extra-special culinary experience such as a natural ‘bio’ breakfast prepared over an open fire rounds off the week.

name: Seefeld´s Tuesday Market
description: Fresh foodstuffs straight from local farms, from agriculture in harmony with nature. No long transport routes, no middlemen - environmentally friendly, healthy and ecologically sustainable for you! Mountain cheese - Tyrolean ‘grey cheese’ - semi-hard cheese - oil-marinated cheese - camembert and many other cheese specialities. Farmhouse butter /Alp butter - quark - yoghurt - eggs. Farmhouse bread - cakes - pasta - various kinds of dumplings - herb salt - herb vinegar - herb oil. Tyrolean ‘Speck’ bacon - various sausage specialities - meat pastes - smoked trout from Leutasch. Honey - honey-based products - jams - chutneys - herb teas - fruit/vegetable juices. Apple juice - cordials - liqueurs - schnaps. Local, seasonal field and garden products that grow here in our region including lettuces - vegetables - herbs - berries - fruit. And special homemade, handcrafted produced made by local farmers’ wives including sheep’s wool, animal hides, knitted socks - herbal pillows - marigold salve - candles - herbal bath products - various arts and crafts. TIP: Tyrolean specialities such as ‘Bratwurst’ sausages and ‘Kiachln’ with cranberry jam or sauerkraut. For further information visit: www.einkaufserlebnis.at.

name: Culinary Festival at the Casino!
description: THE culinary highlight of the year 2017! Do not miss the opportunity, when the Casino Seefeld brings national and international delicacies to Tyrol in cooperation with "Delikatessen Plangger". Experience a tasting of an incredible range of products, amazing rarities of high quality producers from all over the world. Tickets: € 49.00 (including € 30,00 welcome chips).

name: Seefeld market days
description: Top brands at bargain prices at Seefeld´s fashion sale event! At the end of the season, Seefeld’s boutiques and shops clear their shelves to make way for the new collections, giving fashionistas and bargain hunters the chance to purchase highest-quality, brand-name goods at greatly discounted prices. On a culinary level too, shoppers can savour local specialities on offer in the large farmers’ market. With some luck you can win shopping vouchers to the value of € 3,000.

On a culinary level too, shoppers can savour local specialities on offer in the large farmers’ market. With some luck you can win shopping vouchers to the value of € 3,000.

name: Day of motor sport Seefeld 2017
description:
Seefeld’s Autosport Club hosts a second-to-none motorsport event
A wide variety of car models will be competing in pre-specified classes: Sports cars with over 300 horsepower, ‘young’ classic cars with over 200 horsepower and vintage cars over 30 years old. The ‘road-book guided’ rally with lots of action-packed thrills, leads through Tyrol´s unique mountain scenery. 
Programme: 9:30 am, installation of vehicles in Seefeld centre, 10:00 am, start of rally, 5:00 pm, arrival of all cars in the pedestrian area, procession of cars & presentation, prize giving ceremony.

name: 20th TRADITIONAL TYROLEAN CRAFT FAIR
description: Masters of rare crafts, including violin makers, nail smiths, wainwrights and quill embroiderers, are few and far between nowadays. At the 20th Festival of Traditional Tyrolean Handcrafts these ancient artistic traditions are given a new lease of life. Visitors to the festival can watch the masters of their crafts at work. This year men and women from North, South and East Tyrol, and from Salzburg, Carinthia, Vorarlberg and Bavaria, will be demonstrating their valuable handcraft skills. Traditional costume Assoc. and marching bands will be adding colour to the event.

name: "Ambassadors of Music" concert series 2017
description:
The “Ambassadors of Music” Concerts 2017
The much-loved “Ambassadors of Music”, in other words, the various US college bands, will be performing for the 33rd time in the Olympiaregion between June 17 and July 23 2017 and offer an unparalleled range of musical entertainment with their enthusiastic concerts. Entry is free to all concerts!

description:
The “Ambassadors of Music” Concerts 2017
The much-loved “Ambassadors of Music”, in other words, the various US college bands, will be performing for the 33rd time in the Olympiaregion between June 17 and July 23 2017 and offer an unparalleled range of musical entertainment with their enthusiastic concerts. Entry is free to all concerts!

name: Dirndljäger Ball 2017 - music and entertaining ball in traditional costumes
description: The traditional “Dirndljäger Ball” held in the legendary Sportalm in Seefeld - a unique event with an emphasis on traditional costumes, fun and dancing, glamour and fashion, complete with non-stop live music to get everyone in the party spirit. The hosts of this year’s ball, popular Austrian entertainer Gregor Glanz, Charles & Moni Seyrling and Günther Prantl, invite you to enjoy an unforgettable evening of chic Alpine fashion, glamour and live music performed by top acts.

name: Village Festival of Seefeld´s associations
description: Numerous local clubs and associations join forces every year to organise a memorable event with toe-tapping rhythms and mouth-watering treats in Seefeld’s centre. A wide variety of attractions, like dance performances of the local group “Seefelder Plattler“, culinary highlights, as well as live performances, entertainment and live music ensure a fantastic atmosphere during this convivial festival in the centre of Seefeld. Further information is provided in all information offices of Olympiaregion Seefeld and on www.seefeld.com.
